    </div>

    <p>Shilajit is a mineral-rich resinous substance formed over centuries from the decomposition of plant material under geological pressure in high-altitude mountain ranges. Its primary bioactive compound is fulvic acid — a complex organic molecule that functions as an antioxidant, electrolyte, and cellular nutrient transporter. The proposed mechanisms for testosterone support include enhanced Leydig cell function (the testicular cells that produce testosterone), improved mitochondrial energy output, and reduced oxidative damage to reproductive tissues.</p>

