    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Shilajit Gummies for Men</h2>

    <details class="fq"><summary>What is shilajit and why are men taking it?</summary><p>Shilajit is a mineral-rich resin from the Himalayas containing fulvic acid. Men take it for testosterone support (a 2016 study showed 20% increase at 250mg/day for 90 days), energy production (fulvic acid supports mitochondrial ATP), and exercise recovery.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Does shilajit actually increase testosterone?</summary><p>Preliminary evidence says yes. A 2016 Andrologia study found 250mg PrimaVie increased total testosterone by 20.45% and free testosterone by 19.14% after 90 days. However, sample sizes were small (60 men) and larger confirmatory trials are needed.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much shilajit should men take daily?</summary><p>The clinically studied dose is 250-500mg of purified extract daily. Check the fulvic acid content — it should be at least 50% of the extract. Products without a specified dose or fulvic acid percentage should be avoided.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is fulvic acid and why does it matter?</summary><p>Fulvic acid is shilajit's primary bioactive compound (60-80% of purified extracts). It acts as an antioxidant, electrolyte, and nutrient carrier that enhances cellular energy production and mineral absorption. Product quality is defined by fulvic acid concentration.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Is shilajit safe for men?</summary><p>Purified shilajit is safe in clinical trials at 250-500mg for up to 90 days. Never consume raw, unpurified shilajit due to heavy metal contamination risks. Men on blood pressure, diabetes, or blood-thinning medications should consult their physician first.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long does shilajit take to work?</summary><p>Energy benefits may appear within 1-2 weeks. Testosterone effects require 90 days of consistent use — this is the timeline from clinical studies. Exercise recovery improvements may be noticeable within 2-4 weeks.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take shilajit with other supplements?</summary><p>Yes. Common stacks include shilajit + ashwagandha (complementary testosterone pathways), shilajit + CoQ10 (mitochondrial energy), and shilajit + creatine (exercise performance). Fulvic acid may enhance absorption of other supplements.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is the difference between shilajit resin and gummies?</summary><p>Resin is the traditional form — potent but bitter. Gummies contain the same purified extract in a palatable format. When matched for dose and fulvic acid, they deliver equivalent compounds. Gummies are 2-3x more expensive but significantly easier to take consistently.</p></details>

